Warhammer lizards are all sexless (nothing some creative liberties/contrivances cannot solve) ancient alien bio-servants spawned from pools.

They are born fully grown, with many things already known to them (in the big ancient chaos war that nearly destroyed the world warriors were coming out of the pools almost as fast as the demons were coming out of the warp)

There are several varieties that typically serve particular roles. The most numerous are the skinks, they're on the smaller side, like kobolds sorta. They're of average, human level intelligence. They do most of the general labor and fight in battle as light infantry/serve as scouts, beast riders and tamers etc. They're also the middle managers.

The Slann are big fat frogs who are the leaders, they spend most of their time in deep meditation (practically asleep) trying to divine what the ancient aliens wanted them to do. Skinks often talk to them (with either no response at all or something brief and cryptic that they'll easily misinterpret) When awake, they are among the most powerful mages in the world. They try their best to keep the other lizardmen on the course of the Great Plan and preserve the stability of the world, mostly by defending the parts they live in that are full of ancient machinery whose purpose is long forgotten. Without their guidance, the skinks would be liable to start worshipping volcanoes and shit since they aren't up to spending 3 years doing a big think.

The Saurus (pic) are the warrior caste, it is their sole duty. Some veterans become commanders/elite guards, but they're warriors through-and-through.

Then there are the kroxigors. Huge, gator-featured brutes who aren't too bright. They serve as living construction machines/heavy hitters in battle who are just as likely to drop their club and bite as they are to swing it.
